OL,3,C7m hours collectively spent waiting to
OL,4,Cspeak to taxman in 2022-23, report
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,F"HMRC must allow more time for these
OL,8,Fservices to bed in and understand the
OL,9,Fdifference they make before adjusting
OL,10,Fstaffing levels."
OL,12,FDame Meg Hillier, chairwoman of the
OL,13,FPublic Accounts Committee (PAC) said:
OL,14,F"HMRC must hear the frustration of
OL,15,Ftaxpayers and make more realistic
OL,16,Fplans to improve customer service and
OL,17,Fdeliver value for money."
